{
  "texts": [
    "This dependence on a pretrained model, of course, may limit its adaptability to unseen radiolarian morphologies not represented in the fine-tuned dataset.",
    "The most widespread application of DL in micropaleontology has been for the classification of Foraminifera microfossils (refer to Table 9).",
    "Marchant et al. (2020) introduce Base-Cyclic and ResNet-Cyclic networks, based on DCNNs, to classify large Foraminifera image sets.",
    "The networks are tested on the accessible Endless Forams image set (Hsiang et al. 2019) alongside a specialized core-specific dataset for benthic and planktonic species.",
    "The study highlights the efficiency of TL for rapid CNN deployment, aiding manual labeling."
  ]
}